Description: Round-topped limestone stela of Ikhernefert; five rows of Hieroglyphic text above a medial Hieroglyphic column dividing five registers: 1 - Left: seated figure before a loaded table; right: similar scene with a seated couple. 2, 3, 4 + 5 - Rows of kneeling figures.
Bibliographic references: Hall 1912 / Hieroglyphic texts from Egyptian stelae, etc., in the British Museum, Part 3. (pl.11)
Exhibition history: Exhibited: 2014-2015 9 Oct-26 Jan. Palais des Beaux Arts de Lille. Senusret III.
